## Key Constraints
- Work one delegated step at a time: plan, delegate, review, update memory, revise plan, then continue.
- Do not implement before repository inspection and web research establish facts.
- No user-level or global settings in final instructions; everything must be per-project/workspace-local.
- Do not assume OpenCode, VS Code, or Codex behavior. Use official docs/web research and mark unsupported/unknown features clearly.
- Do not expose or copy secrets from local configs such as `opencode.json`.
- Do not commit unless explicitly requested.

